             <h2>
              Welcome
             </h2>
             <div>
              If you have an immediate need of money, you may think of payday loans as a good way to get the cash you need. However, you need to be aware of their drawbacks and make sure they are the right decision for your situation. Here is some information on the pros and cons of payday loans.

The best thing about payday loans is that they can give you quick money in an emergency. However, you should understand that this will only happen when you are able to repay the loan in full. A payday loan is typically a short, temporary unsecured cash advance with very high interest rates.

These short-term loans can be expensive, so you should only use them if you have to have the money ASAP. When you are able to repay the payday loans in full within a set amount of time, you are allowed to use it again.

While the process of obtaining the loan is relatively easy, the fees can be a little bit high. Usually you will pay a one-time application fee. Then there is a regular fee that will be added on at the end of the month. You will also need to pay a late fee if you are late paying the loan.

The downside to this type of loan is that you are risking your credit score. This is because your income will be checked to see if you qualify for the loan or not. You should be careful that you don't use your credit card too frequently. Instead, take your paycheck and apply it towards your loan.
             </div>
             <div>
             </div>
             <div>
              The staff of Business and Finance supports the
              <a href="http://www.umflint.edu/chancellor/mission-vision">
               Mission and Vision of the Flint Campus
              </a>
              .  More specifically and personal to our organization:
             </div>
             <ul>
              <li>
               <strong>
                VISION:  "the why":
               </strong>
               We believe that an 
education at ascashapply.com can enhance the lives of students, families, and 
ultimately the Flint community.  This is
               <em>
                "the Michigan Difference"
               </em>
               and will result in transformational growth for all.
              </li>
              <li>
               <strong>
                MISSION:  "the how":
               </strong>

                "Serving the Blue, Serving U".

              </li>
              <li>
               <strong>

               </strong>
               Delivery of the deep 
expertise in our various areas of specialty; servicing many as the 
provider of choice and employer of choice...and to do so with a "
               <em>
                warranty"
               </em>
               ...we strive to make it right, or at a minimum, understandable.
              </li>
             </ul>
             <p>
              The reason you will find payday loans at a low interest rate is because you will be guaranteed a loan regardless of whether you pay it back or not. Because of this, many people are able to obtain their loan on a payday without worrying about being rejected by lenders.

When you are able to make timely payments on your loan, you may be able to use it again. If you don't pay your loan on time, you will lose your ability to take a payday loan. Therefore, you should keep up with your payments on your loan and make it back in a timely manner.

In addition to the risk that you take by taking a payday loan on credit, you may also lose out on saving if you don't pay your loan back on time. This can be an embarrassing situation, especially if you have bad credit. If you can avoid the pitfalls that are associated with these types of loans, then they can be a good option for people who need quick cash.

When using short term loans, you should also consider your options for consolidating your debts. Debt consolidation loans can be used for paying off other loans and bills. Consolidation loans are a great way to put all of your monthly bills under one roof.
             </p>
